Steinhoff International, Universal Industries: South African Stock Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-11T06:34:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/steinhoff-universal-industries-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South
Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and
prices are from the last close.  South  Africa ’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined to
the lowest since Dec. 1, losing 921.43, or 2.90 percent, to
30,898.94 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL SJ): Oil declined for a fourth day,
dropping as much as 1.1 percent, to $101 a barrel. Sasol, the
largest producer of motor fuels made from coal, declined 15.02
rand, or 4 percent, to 386.99 rand.    Steinhoff International Holdings Ltd. (SHF)  : Africa’s
largest furniture maker said its 450 million euro ($621 million)
convertible bond was oversubscribed. Steinhoff declined 70
cents, or 2.8 percent, to 24.11 rand.  Universal Industries Corp. (UNI SJ): The supplier of ovens
and fridges said earnings per share excluding one-time items for
the year ended December rose 19 percent. The company increased
its dividend by 17 percent to 3.5 cents. The stock was unchanged
at 1.40 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 4.5 percent to $24.83
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) slipped 4.3 percent to $45.48.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) fell 4.3 percent to $73.92. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) lost 2.7 percent to $4.72. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) declined 2.7 percent to $17.11. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) lost 1.5 percent to $12.13. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) dropped 5.5 percent to $27.41. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) slipped 5
percent to $4.96.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL)   lost 4.7 percent to
$52.12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
